# Blog Markdown Editing Rules

## Frontmatter Protection

Blog posts use YAML frontmatter delimited by `---`. When editing these files:

1. **NEVER** insert blank lines inside the frontmatter block (between the opening `---` and closing `---`).
2. **NEVER** prepend `##` or any Markdown syntax to frontmatter fields.
3. Always verify the frontmatter structure remains intact after any edit.

Correct format:
```
---
title: "Post Title"
date: 2026-01-01
---
```

## HTML Block Protection

Some blog posts contain `<details>/<summary>` collapsible sections and other raw HTML blocks.

1. **NEVER** remove `<details>`, `<summary>`, `</summary>`, `</details>` tags during edits.
2. **NEVER** remove `<!-- markdownlint-disable -->` / `<!-- markdownlint-restore -->` comment pairs.
3. When editing content inside a `<details>` block, always preserve the opening and closing tags.
4. After any edit, verify all HTML structural tags are still present.

## Square Bracket Escaping

In Markdown, `[text]` is parsed as a link reference. When square brackets are used as literal labels (not links), they must be escaped: `\[text\]`.
